{
  "analysis": "The build succeeded and doom runs, finding the WAD file and printing startup messages. However, it crashes during R_Init (PC jumps to 0x0). The most likely issues are: 1) heap too small (8MB may not be enough for all doom allocations), 2) math stubs causing issues, or 3) some other runtime issue. Let me debug further.",
  "plan": "Increase heap size to 32MB, add debugging to R_Init, and try again.",
  "commands": [
    {"keystrokes": "sed -i 's|8 \\* 1024 \\* 1024|32 * 1024 * 1024|' /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/my_stdlib.c\n", "duration": 0.1},
    {"keystrokes": "grep -n 'heap\\[' /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/my_stdlib.c\n", "duration": 0.1},
    {"keystrokes": "grep -n 'R_Init' /app/doomgeneric/doomgeneric/r_main.c | head -10\n", "duration": 0.1}
  ]
}
